    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Psalms",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 51,
        "summary": "David pleads for forgiveness after he went in to Bathsheba\u2014He pleads, Create in me a clean heart, and renew a right spirit within me.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Have mercy upon me, O God, according to thy lovingkindness: according unto the multitude of thy tender mercies blot out my transgressions.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 25:7.",
                        "start": 5,
                        "end": 10
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Kindness.",
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 58
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Acts 3:19.",
                        "start": 111,
                        "end": 119
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sin.",
                        "start": 123,
                        "end": 137
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Wash me throughly from mine iniquity, and cleanse me from my sin.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 26:29 (29\u201330). TG\u00a0Purification.",
                        "start": 42,
                        "end": 49
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For I acknowledge my transgressions: and my sin is ever before me.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Confession.",
                        "start": 6,
                        "end": 17
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sin.",
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 47
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 50
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Against thee, thee only, have I sinned, and done this evil in thy sight: that thou mightest be justified when thou speakest, and be clear when thou judgest.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Sam. 12:13 (9\u201314).",
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 38
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Rom. 3:4; D&C 97:2.",
                        "start": 95,
                        "end": 104
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 53
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 125,
                        "end": 128
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Behold, I was shapen in iniquity; and in sin did my mother conceive me.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Conceived in Sin.",
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 67
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Behold, thou desirest truth in the inward parts: and in the hidden part thou shalt make me to know wisdom.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 71
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Purge me with hyssop, and I shall be clean: wash me, and I shall be whiter than snow.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Num. 19:18.",
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 20
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Make me to hear joy and gladness; that the bones which thou hast broken may rejoice.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 38
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 54
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Hide thy face from my sins, and blot out all mine iniquities.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Create in me a clean heart, O God; and renew a right spirit within me.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Cleanliness; Purification; Repent.",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 20
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Lam. 5:21.",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 44
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Cast me not away from thy presence; and take not thy holy spirit from me.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Death, Spiritual, First.",
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 34
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Holy Ghost, Loss of.",
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 64
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Restore unto me the joy of thy salvation; and uphold me with thy free spirit.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 56,
                        "end": 64
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Then will I teach transgressors thy ways; and sinners shall be converted unto thee.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Conversion.",
                        "start": 63,
                        "end": 72
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 4
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Deliver me from bloodguiltiness, O God, thou God of my salvation: and my tongue shall sing aloud of thy righteousness.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Deliver.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 7
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 66,
                        "end": 69
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "O Lord, open thou my lips; and my mouth shall shew forth thy praise.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For thou desirest not sacrifice; else would I give it: thou delightest not in burnt offering.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Sam. 15:22.",
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 31
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 51,
                        "end": 54
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The sacrifices of God are a broken spirit: a broken and a contrite heart, O God, thou wilt not despise.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Hosea 14:2 (1\u20133); 3\u00a0Ne. 9:20 (19\u201320).",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 14
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Contrite Heart.",
                        "start": 58,
                        "end": 72
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 25
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Do good in thy good pleasure unto Zion: build thou the walls of Jerusalem.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Pleasure.",
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 28
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Then shalt thou be pleased with the sacrifices of righteousness, with burnt offering and whole burnt offering: then shall they offer bullocks upon thine altar.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}